---
import StarlightPage from "@astrojs/starlight/components/StarlightPage.astro";
import Tags from "../components/Tags.astro";
---

<StarlightPage frontmatter={{ title: "External resources" }}>
  <style>
    .skeleton {
      display: inline-block;
      height: 1em;
      background-color: var(--sl-color-gray-5);
      border-radius: 8px;
      animation: pulse 2s cubic-bezier(0.4, 0, 0.6, 1) infinite;
    }

    @keyframes pulse {
      0%,
      100% {
        opacity: 1;
      }
      50% {
        opacity: 0.5;
      }
    }
  </style>
  See guided examples of adding features to your Astro project, submitted by our
  community members! <a href="https://docs.astro.build/en/recipes/"
    >Astro recipes</a
  >
  are typically short, focused how-to guides that walk a reader through completing
  a working example of a specific task. Recipes are a great way to add new features
  or behavior to your Astro project by following step-by-step instructions! Other
  guides might explain concepts related to an area of content, such as using images
  or working with MDX.

  {
    /* :::tip[Add your own!]
  Have you written a recipe for Astro? [Edit this page](https://github.com/withastro/docs/edit/main/src/content/docs/en/community-resources/content.mdx) and add your link in the appropriate section!
  ::: */
  }

  <hr style="margin-block: 20px;" />

  <Tags server:defer>
    <div slot="fallback">
      <span class="skeleton" style="width:100%; height: 100px;"></span>
      <span class="skeleton" style="width:100%; height: 30px;"></span>
      <span class="skeleton" style="width:100%; height: 150px;"></span>
      <span class="skeleton" style="width:100%; height: 150px;"></span>
    </div>
  </Tags>
</StarlightPage>
